The paper focuses on building an intelligent tutoring system that improves student learning outcomes by analyzing their face and gestures. This involves modeling the temporal structure of video sequences of students solving math problems using a recurrent neural network architecture. The paper also presents a novel transfer learning facial affect representation and a user-personalized training scheme. Given these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
